 2008, Junger and photographer Tim Hetherington embedded with the 173rd Airborne Brigade Combat Team in Afghanistan. They spent intensive time with the soldiers at the Restrepo outpost in the Korengal Valley, which saw more combat than any other part of Afghanistan. The experience became Junger&#39;s book&nbsp;<a href=\\"http://www.amazon.com/WAR-Sebastian-Junger/dp/B00CVDYMUI\\" target=\\"_blank\\"><em>WAR</em></a>, and the documentary &quot;<a href=\\"http://restrepothemovie.com/\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Restrepo</a>,&quot; which was nominated for the Academy Award for Best Documentary in 2011.</p><p class=\\"p1\\">Junger and Hetherington planned to make a second documentary on the topic, &quot;<a href=\\"https://korengalthemovie.com/\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Korengal</a>,&quot; meant to help soldiers and civilians alike understand the fear, courage and complexity involved in combat. It&#39;s a project that Junger decided to carry on after Hetherington was killed in Libya while covering the civil war there. Junger self-financed and released the film.</p>", "slug": "sebastian_junger", "whotheyare": "The author of \\"The Perfect Storm\\" and the director of the documentaries \\"Restrepo\\" and \\"Korengal,\\" Sebastian Junger tells non-fiction stories with grit and emotion.", "whatotherssay": "", "id": 1901, "photo_url": "https://pe.tedcdn.com/images/ted/754f2a41f233633d247b8d21612d9fca225e0e85_254x191.jpg"}], "title": "Our lonely society makes it hard to come home from war", "take_action": [], "comments": 27124, "more_resources": [{"status": "approved", "publisher": "Twelve", "start_at": null, "author": "Sebastian Junger", "headline": "Tribe: On Homecoming and Belonging", "link_url": "http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1455566381/ref=as_li_tf_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=0520271440&linkCode=as2&tag=teco06-20", "published": true, "eyebrow": null, "end_at": null, "image_url": "http://pe.tedcdn.com/images/ted/093728b7e349cde97b810655a514c872453987fa_1500x